                            <comment id="16241268" author="akolb" created="Tue, 7 Nov 2017 00:57:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It isn&apos;t just the initial extra slash, but multiple slashes in the middle present similar issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16241352" author="akolb" created="Tue, 7 Nov 2017 02:11:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that when we store paths in the database, we always remove the leading slash, so all paths do not have it. Worth adding a comment (and possibly a precondition check) somewhere.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16241356" author="akolb" created="Tue, 7 Nov 2017 02:12:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is a bug, but if you want to repurpose it for adding comment/precondition please feel free to keep it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
